    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 16.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in
                                        Japan</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Kanagawa</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 30, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            received an official notification that the Tycoon, early next month,
                            will visit Kioto for the purpose of meeting the Mikado.</p>
                <pb facs="0501" n="481" xml:id="pg_481"/>
                <p>The visit last year had been without precedent for three hundred years.
                            This second visit is more extraordinary still. It is hoped it will tend
                            to a more cordial understanding between the Mikado and Tycoon, and to a
                            more favorable foreign policy.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBERT. H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident in
                                    Japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
